  "response": "The time required to learn typing varies depending on several factors:\n\n1. Initial skill level\n- Complete beginner: 2-3 months\n- Some basic keyboard familiarity: 1-2 months\n\n2. Practice frequency\n- 15-30 minutes daily: Faster progress\n- Occasional practice: Slower improvement\n\n3. Learning method\n- Structured typing courses: More efficient\n- Self-learning: Can take longer\n\n4. Target typing speed\n- Basic proficiency (40-50 WPM): 1-2 months\n- Intermediate skills (60-70 WPM): 3-6 months\n- Professional level (80+ WPM): 6-12 months\n\n5. Individual factors\n- Age\n- Motor skills\n- Dedication\n- Natural aptitude\n\nTips for faster learning:\n- Use online typing tutorials\n- Practice consistently\n- Use touch typing techniques\n- Take typing tests\n- Be patient with yourself\n\nMost people can achieve reasonable typing skills within 2-3 months of regular practice.",
